    <node id="The expected approach for awarding A-level and GCSE qualifications in Wales this summer, following the ministerial direction issued to Qualifications Wales, involves teachers submitting estimated grades based on a range of data and professional judgment. Teachers will also rank students in order of performance. These submitted grades will then be moderated by Qualifications Wales, both within individual schools/colleges and across the nation, to ensure fairness and consistency. This process aims to award students a grade that reflects their performance and allows them to make decisions about their future, while maintaining a robust qualifications system. The approach aims to balance recognizing pupils' coursework progress with their potential performance in exams by considering a range of data and professional judgment." />
