    <node id="Based on the meeting transcript, the Welsh Government is aware that some children with special educational needs (SEN) may not respond as well to remote learning. However, no specific mention has been made about a relaxation of lockdown rules for these children. Instead, the focus is on ensuring appropriate referral mechanisms are in place for teachers or anyone who has concerns about a child, and that schools should continue to identify vulnerable children and refer them to children's services if needed. There is also an expectation for schools to remain in contact with children during this time. While there has been no explicit mention of relaxing lockdown rules for children with SEN, the Welsh Government seems open to considering measures to support these children in future phases of education in the new normal." />
