    <edge source="1. Discussions are taking place between the Welsh Government, NUS Wales, and counterparts across the UK regarding financial support for students impacted by changes in their study arrangements due to the pandemic.&#10;2. There will be no change to student support payments for students who have left their universities and decided to go home.&#10;3. The Welsh Government continues to pay Education Maintenance Allowance (EMA) at this time for FE students who are eligible, even though there is an attendance requirement which is not appropriate to enforce at the moment.&#10;4. Officials are in touch with UCAS, and the Welsh Minister for Education has had meetings with representatives of the Welsh higher education sector to discuss these matters.&#10;5. The Welsh Government advises students to have discussions with their accommodation providers about waiving or partially waiving accommodation fees where appropriate.&#10;6. The Welsh Government is working with representatives of the HE sector to include them in these approaches and keep them apprised of the situation, as they may wish to implement similar measures within their own institutions." target="1. In response to the financial challenges faced by students due to the pandemic, the Welsh Government, along with Universities Wales and representatives of the Welsh higher education sector, are aiming to provide stability for the next academic year and support the sector through these challenging times by releasing as much money as possible to help universities get through this initial period of difficulty. Students are also advised to discuss waiving or partially waiving accommodation fees with their providers.&#10;2. Discussions are taking place between relevant bodies in Wales, Northern Ireland, Scotland, and the Westminster Government, as well as UCAS, to address issues related to student entry into universities due to the pandemic. This includes discussions on the moratorium on unconditional offers for university admission.&#10;3. The Welsh Government is working with NUS Wales and counterparts across the UK to provide financial support for students impacted by changes in their study arrangements due to the pandemic, including issues related to accommodation costs.&#10;4. Some universities have already shown initiative by waiving or partially waiving accommodation fees where appropriate, which has been welcomed by NUS Wales. The Welsh Government continues to engage in dialogue with NUS Wales and counterparts across the country to explore further support for students at this time.">
