    <edge source="1. Discussions are taking place between the Welsh Government, NUS Wales, and counterparts across the UK regarding financial support for students impacted by changes in their study arrangements due to the pandemic.&#10;2. There will be no change to student support payments for students who have left their universities and decided to go home.&#10;3. The Welsh Government continues to pay Education Maintenance Allowance (EMA) at this time for FE students who are eligible, even though there is an attendance requirement which is not appropriate to enforce at the moment.&#10;4. Officials are in touch with UCAS, and the Welsh Minister for Education has had meetings with representatives of the Welsh higher education sector to discuss these matters.&#10;5. The Welsh Government advises students to have discussions with their accommodation providers about waiving or partially waiving accommodation fees where appropriate.&#10;6. The Welsh Government is working with representatives of the HE sector to include them in these approaches and keep them apprised of the situation, as they may wish to implement similar measures within their own institutions." target="1. The Welsh Government, in collaboration with Universities Wales and representatives of the Welsh higher education sector, is aiming to provide stability for the next academic year and support the sector through these challenging times by releasing as much money as possible to help universities get through this initial period of difficulty. This aligns with one of the key proposals from Universities UK, which emphasizes the need for financial support to ensure university sustainability.&#10;2. The Welsh Government is also participating in discussions with relevant bodies in Wales, Northern Ireland, Scotland, and the Westminster Government, as well as UCAS, to address issues related to student entry into universities due to the pandemic. This includes discussions on the moratorium on unconditional offers for university admission, which is another concern raised by Universities UK.&#10;3. Additionally, the Welsh Government is working with NUS Wales and counterparts across the UK to provide financial support for students impacted by changes in their study arrangements due to the pandemic. This addresses another issue raised by Universities UK, which highlights the need for student financial support during this time. The Welsh Government's efforts demonstrate a commitment to addressing the challenges faced by both universities and students in light of the pandemic, with measures that are consistent with the proposals put forward by Universities UK.">
