    <edge source="1. In response to the financial challenges faced by students due to the pandemic, the Welsh Government, along with Universities Wales and representatives of the Welsh higher education sector, are aiming to provide stability for the next academic year and support the sector through these challenging times by releasing as much money as possible to help universities get through this initial period of difficulty. Students are also advised to discuss waiving or partially waiving accommodation fees with their providers.&#10;2. Discussions are taking place between relevant bodies in Wales, Northern Ireland, Scotland, and the Westminster Government, as well as UCAS, to address issues related to student entry into universities due to the pandemic. This includes discussions on the moratorium on unconditional offers for university admission.&#10;3. The Welsh Government is working with NUS Wales and counterparts across the UK to provide financial support for students impacted by changes in their study arrangements due to the pandemic, including issues related to accommodation costs.&#10;4. Some universities have already shown initiative by waiving or partially waiving accommodation fees where appropriate, which has been welcomed by NUS Wales. The Welsh Government continues to engage in dialogue with NUS Wales and counterparts across the country to explore further support for students at this time." target="1. The Welsh Government, in collaboration with Universities Wales and representatives of the Welsh higher education sector, is aiming to provide stability for the next academic year and support the sector through these challenging times by releasing as much money as possible to help universities get through this initial period of difficulty. This aligns with one of the key proposals from Universities UK, which emphasizes the need for financial support to ensure university sustainability.&#10;2. The Welsh Government is also participating in discussions with relevant bodies in Wales, Northern Ireland, Scotland, and the Westminster Government, as well as UCAS, to address issues related to student entry into universities due to the pandemic. This includes discussions on the moratorium on unconditional offers for university admission, which is another concern raised by Universities UK.&#10;3. Additionally, the Welsh Government is working with NUS Wales and counterparts across the UK to provide financial support for students impacted by changes in their study arrangements due to the pandemic. This addresses another issue raised by Universities UK, which highlights the need for student financial support during this time. The Welsh Government's efforts demonstrate a commitment to addressing the challenges faced by both universities and students in light of the pandemic, with measures that are consistent with the proposals put forward by Universities UK.">
